HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 215
BY REPRESENTATIVE DANA HENRY
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Designates April 29, 2026, as Hospital Day in Louisiana
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate April 29, 2026, as Hospital Day in Louisiana.
3 WHEREAS, Hospital Day is a celebration that serves as a reminder that hospitals in
4 Louisiana are cornerstones of the communities, and that hospitals serve people in every
5 community from all walks of life; and
6 WHEREAS, Hospital Day celebrates hospitals and the frontline caregivers who
7 support the health of their communities through dedication and compassionate care; and
8 WHEREAS, the theme for Hospital Day this year is "Advancing Louisiana's Health
9 Through Community Programs, Partnerships, and Innovations"; and
10 WHEREAS, hospitals and health systems in Louisiana play an integral role in
11 providing vital healthcare services to all residents of Louisiana, twenty-four hours a day,
12 seven days a week, three hundred sixty-five days a year, through acute care and specialty
13 hospital services; and
14 WHEREAS, hospitals today are multi-dimensional environments that offer every
15 medical specialty, and also focus on population health, prevention, and wellness; and
16 WHEREAS, in addition to providing critical healthcare services, Louisiana hospitals
17 and health systems are economic drivers in the state directly employing more than one
18 hundred thousand people with an annual payroll of more than seven and a half billion dollars
19 and contributing more than thirty-eight billion dollars to Louisiana's economy overall
20 through creating and supporting more than three hundred thousand direct and indirect jobs
21 statewide in industries such as construction and retail; and
